# ── Secrets ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# config.json holds live Pexels / Pixabay / Gemini keys. Never commit it.
# config.example.json is the safe template — that one IS tracked.
config.json

# Google Cloud service-account key for Vertex AI. This is a PRIVATE KEY — never
# commit it. Keep the JSON in keys/ (ignored) and point vertex_service_account
# at it, or store it outside the repo entirely.
keys/
*service-account*.json
*service_account*.json
*-sa.json

# ── Generated and downloadable ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# All of this rebuilds itself from the sheets. Committing it would push the
# repo into the gigabytes and GitHub rejects any single file over 100 MB.
#
# Each project now lives in projects/<id>/{sheets,work,out}/. The sheets are
# the source of truth and ARE tracked (small text, they sync across machines);
# work/ and out/ are the heavy, rebuildable parts and are ignored — both in the
# new per-project location and in the old flat one, until every machine has run
# the one-time migration.
.venv/
cache/
work/
out/
projects/*/work/
projects/*/out/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.egg-info/
build/
dist/

# ── Reference audio ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Tracked. These are LibriVox recordings (public domain), they are small, and
# having them travel with the repo means a fresh clone can voice immediately.
# If you ever add a clip you do NOT hold redistribution rights to, add it here
# by name and copy it between machines by hand instead.

# ── Music ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Background tracks are licensed to you, not necessarily redistributable.
music/*
!music/README.txt

# ── OS clutter ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
